HEADWORD: Farsighted
<hw>Far"sight`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Seeing to great distance; hence, of good judgment regarding the
remote effects of actions; sagacious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Hypermetropic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Farsightedness</ent>⟦br⟧
